Scrum
============
- It is the framework through which the software is built using the agile model principles.
- The people involved in the scrum are called as 'scrum team'.

User Story
===============
It is a requirement of the module/feature/functionality of the software.

Story Point
===========
It is rough estimation of the efforts required to complete user story

Epic
=============
It is a collection of User stories. It is a complete set of requirements of the software.

Product Backlog
====================
It is the list of user stories that need to be picked up, upon which the team needs to work.

Sprint
=============
It is the time period given to complete the picked-up user stories from product backlog.
Ex : Usually it will be of 2 weeks

Sprint Planning Meeting
===========================
- It is a meeting in which it is decided which user stories need to be picked up for work from product backlog, which user stories need to be assigned to whom both from testing and developement prespective & what should be the duration of the Sprint.
- This meeting will happen before the start of sprint.

Scrum meeting/ Stand-Up meeting
=====================================
It is a meeting that is conducted on a daily basis during the sprint where everyone will give updates on three points
a. What did i do yesterday
b. What is my plan for today
c. Challenges/Blockers  i am facing

Sprint Review meeting
===================
- This meeting is conducted at the end of the sprint.
- In this meeting, each team member's work on the assigned user stories will be reviewed.

Sprint Retrospective meeting
===================================
It is a meeting that is conducted at the end of the sprint, in which sprint analysis will be done, by discussing on below 3 points.
a. What went well
b. What didn't go well
c.  Actions to be taken for improvement

Note : All the meetings will be conducted by manager/lead from dev & testing, audience will be from both teams.